        public void treeToString()

      • compareTrees

        private boolean compareTrees(NumericBinaryTree nbt1,
                             NumericBinaryTree nbt2)
        Utility to compare two trees for shape and contents.
        Parameters:
        nbt1 - first tree for comparison
        nbt2 - second tree for comparison
        Returns:
        true if and only if both are non-null, have the same number of nodes and same height, and if non-empty then also have equal root values, and if present both the left children and right children also return true to this predicate
